      "Automatic day-date built on the ETA 2824-2 base train. It is the 13''' (29.00 mm) variant: the 2824-2/2836-2 base movement (11.5''', 25.60 mm) plus an enlargement ring (ETA part 926) and casing clamp (part 166) that bring the outside diameter to 29.00 mm. Day is a panoramic/arc weekday window at 12 o'clock (full spelling) with date window at 3 o'clock; both are quickset. 28,800 A/h, 50 deg lift angle, ETACHRON regulator, bidirectional ball-bearing automatic winding, hand-windable and hacking (stop-seconds). Power reserve listed as 38 h on older ETA sheets / 42 h on the current ETA site. CORRECTION TO HINT: the ETA technical communication (CT 2801-2) lists BOTH the 2834-2 and 2836-2 at the same 5.05 mm movement height, so the 2834-2 is NOT thicker than the 2836-2; the real difference is the 29 mm enlarged diameter and the arc day-at-12 layout (the 2836-2 is 25.6 mm with a rectangular day-at-3). Hand bores (shared with 2824-2 base): hour 1.50 mm, minute 0.90 mm, sweep second 0.25 mm. Sofly lists it as automatic-only, but the 2824-2 base is hand-windable and Caliber Corner confirms hand-winding.",
